    <note>Ren(1) Zhiji [3427] According to Liu(2) Qi [3583], since he had many kinsmen (zongzu) in Dingtao, his post as county accountant (zhubu) was made particularly difficult. His marriage to Xi(3) Ping's [18256] daughter was praised by the kindred group (yindang). When she died, he married her cousin (modified sororate). Zhiji's son-in-law was Liu Qi's younger brother's son, unnamed Liu(2) A [18274], and two Ren, Shao and Zhao (CBD, 1, 651 [not in dataset]) were early Southern Song Linjiang residents and have notices composed by Zhou Bida. Liu Qi, WJ, 8.97-98. CBD, 1, 656.</note>
